 success than in New York. This documentary from Marc Levin examines the effect of the increased globalization of clothing manufacturing on the city's once-thriving garment district. The economic and social forces that have transformed the industry and the nation over the last century are explored through interviews with those who have experienced as many ups and downs as hemlines, including Fern Mallis, the creator of Fashion Week; the designer Isaac Mizrahi; Joe Raico, above, a fabric cutter; Irving Rousso, a rags-to-riches garmento; and Lisa Nussbaum, a cousin of Sadie Nussbaum, one of 146 people who died in the Triangle Shirtwaist fire of 1911. 7 P.M. (Showtime) BUD GREENSPAN PRESENTS: BEIJING 2008 -- AMERICA'S OLYMPIC GLORY In this documentary about the Olympics, Mr. Greenspan goes behind the scenes in China and interviews American athletes and medalists including Jason Lezak, the swim team captain; the gymnast Nastia Liukin; Brenda Villa, the captain of the water polo team; and the fencers Keeth and Erinn Smart.","abstract":null,"print_page":"6","blog":[],"source":"The New York Times","multimedia":[],"headline":{"main":"What's On Today"},"keywords":[],"pub_date":"2009-10-19T00:00:00Z","document_type":"article","news_desk":"The Arts\/Cultural Desk","section_name":"Arts","subsection_name":null,"byline":{"person":[{"organization":"","role":"reported","rank":1,"firstname":"Kathryn","lastname":"SHATTUCK"}],"original":"By KATHRYN SHATTUCK"},"type_of_material":"News","_id":"4fd274738eb7c8105d832a51","word_count":651},{"web_url":"http:\/\/query.nytimes.com\/gst\/fullpage.html?res=9802E5D61131F93AA35752C1A96F9C8B63","snippet":"International     SUICIDE BLAST IN PAKISTAN KILLS ANTI-TALIBAN MAYOR  ","lead_paragraph":"International SUICIDE BLAST IN PAKISTAN KILLS ANTI-TALIBAN MAYOR","abstract":null,"print_page":"2","blog":[],"source":"The New York Times","multimedia":[],"headline":{"main":"Inside the Times"},"keywords":[],"pub_date":"2009-11-09T00:00:00Z","document_type":